<item>
            <title>[SOLR-16631] solr.shardsWhitelist solr.allowUrls - hostnames should be treated in case insensitive way</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16631</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Given that hostnames should be case insensitive (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc3986#section-6.2.2.1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;rfc3986;section-6.2.2.1&lt;/a&gt;), the check for should also consider hostnames in urls in a case insentive way.&lt;br/&gt;
That is not the case (not in Solr 8 and not after refactoring in Solr 9).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Most people are using always lowercases for hostnames in urls, so probably not encountered that often and there is an easy and quick fix by changing the parameter to match the actual cases used in the hostname, hence priority is &quot;Minor&quot;. But still, it is better to comply with well-established rules.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Easy test via changing 1 char to uppercase in the hostname of the unit test AllowListUrlCheckerTest.testSingleHost().&lt;br/&gt;
E.g. test result:&lt;br/&gt;
org.apache.solr.common.SolrException: URL &lt;a href=&quot;http://abc-1.com:8983/solr&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://abc-1.Com:8983/solr&lt;/a&gt; is neither a live node of the cluster nor in the configured &apos;allowUrls&apos; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;abc-1.com:8983&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15340&quot; title=&quot;rename shardsWhitelist to allowUrls and move to top of solr.xml&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-15340&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-15340&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; renamed solr.shardsWhitelist to solr.allowUrls&lt;/p&gt;</description>
